From: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2020 14:30:17 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu/debugfs: fix ref count leak when
 pm_runtime_get_sync fails
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.8.2
Git-commit: 9eee152aab56d374edb9ad21b3db05f5cdda2fe6

[ Upstream commit 9eee152aab56d374edb9ad21b3db05f5cdda2fe6 ]

The call to pm_runtime_get_sync increments the counter even in case of
failure, leading to incorrect ref count.
In case of failure, decrement the ref count before returning.

Acked-by: Evan Quan <evan.quan@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
